Authors: 1,Stephen,King,1947-09-21,null,American,"Stephen King is a prolific American author of horror, supernatural fiction, suspense, crime, science-fiction, and fantasy novels."
2,J.K.,Rowling,1965-07-31,null,British,"J.K. Rowling is a British author, philanthropist, film producer, and screenwriter, best known for writing the Harry Potter fantasy series."

3,George,Orwell,1903-06-25,1950-01-21,British,"George Orwell was an English novelist, essayist, journalist, and critic. His work is characterized by lucid prose, biting social criticism, opposition to totalitarianism, and outspoken support of democratic socialism."

4,Jane,Austen,1775-12-16,1817-07-18,British,"Jane Austen was an English novelist known primarily for her six major novels, which interpret, critique, and comment upon the British landed gentry at the end of the 18th century."

5,Ernest,Hemingway,1899-07-21,1961-07-02,American,"Ernest Hemingway was an American novelist, short-story writer, and journalist. His economical and understated style had a strong influence on 20th-century fiction."

6,Agatha,Christie,1890-09-15,1976-01-12,British,"Agatha Christie was an English writer known for her 66 detective novels and 14 short story collections, particularly those featuring Hercule Poirot and Miss Marple."

7,William,Shakespeare,1564-04-26,1616-04-23,English,"William Shakespeare was an English playwright, poet, and actor, widely regarded as the greatest writer in the English language and the world's greatest dramatist."

8,Leo,Tolstoy,1828-09-09,1910-11-20,Russian,"Leo Tolstoy was a Russian writer who is regarded as one of the greatest authors of all time. He is best known for the novels War and Peace and Anna Karenina."

9,Mark,Twain,1835-11-30,1910-04-21,American,"Mark Twain was an American writer, humorist, entrepreneur, publisher, and lecturer. He was lauded as the 'greatest humorist the United States has produced'."

10,Virginia,Woolf,1882-01-25,1941-03-28,British,"Virginia Woolf was an English writer, considered one of the most important modernist 20th-century authors and a pioneer in the use of stream of consciousness as a narrative device."
11,Gabriel García,Márquez,1927-03-06,2014-04-17,Colombian,"Gabriel García Márquez was a Colombian novelist, short-story writer, screenwriter, and journalist, known for his magical realism."

12,Toni,Morrison,1931-02-18,2019-08-05,American,"Toni Morrison was an American novelist, essayist, book editor, and college professor. Her novels are known for their epic themes, vivid dialogue, and richly detailed African-American characters."

13,Haruki,Murakami,1949-01-12,null,Japanese,"Haruki Murakami is a Japanese writer. His books and stories have been bestsellers in Japan and internationally, with his work translated into 50 languages."

14,Charles,Dickens,1812-02-07,1870-06-09,British,"Charles Dickens was an English writer and social critic. He created some of the world's best-known fictional characters and is regarded by many as the greatest novelist of the Victorian era."
15,F. Scott,Fitzgerald,1896-09-24,1940-12-21,American,"F. Scott Fitzgerald was an American novelist, short story writer, and screenwriter. He is best known for his novels depicting the Jazz Age."

16,Herman,Melville,1819-08-01,1891-09-28,American,"Herman Melville was an American novelist, short story writer, and poet of the American Renaissance period. He is best known for his whaling novel Moby Dick."
17,Mary,Shelley,1797-08-30,1851-02-01,British,"Mary Shelley was an English novelist who wrote the Gothic novel Frankenstein; or, The Modern Prometheus."
18,Victor,Hugo,1802-02-26,1885-05-22,French,"Victor Hugo was a French poet, novelist, and dramatist of the Romantic movement. He is considered one of the greatest and best-known French writers."
19,Albert,Camus,1913-11-07,1960-01-04,French,"Albert Camus was a French philosopher, author, and journalist. He was awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature at the age of 44."
20,Chinua,Achebe,1930-11-16,2013-03-21,Nigerian,"Chinua Achebe was a Nigerian novelist, poet, and critic who is regarded as the dominant figure in modern African literature."

21,Isabel,Allende,1942-08-02,null,Chilean,"Isabel Allende is a Chilean writer. Allende, whose works sometimes contain aspects of 'magical realism', is known for her novels such as The House of the Spirits."
22,Kazuo,Ishiguro,1954-11-08,null,British,"Kazuo Ishiguro is a British novelist, screenwriter, and short-story writer. He was born in Nagasaki, Japan, and moved to England in 1960."

23,Margaret,Atwood,1939-11-18,null,Canadian,"Margaret Atwood is a Canadian poet, novelist, literary critic, essayist, and environmental activist. She has written numerous novels, including The Handmaid's Tale."
24,Umberto,Eco,1932-01-05,2016-02-19,Italian,"Umberto Eco was an Italian medievalist, philosopher, semiotician, novelist, cultural critic, and political and social commentator."
25,Jorge Luis,Borges,1899-08-24,1986-06-14,Argentinian,"Jorge Luis Borges was an Argentine short-story writer, essayist, poet, and translator, and a key figure in Spanish-language literature."
26,Franz,Kafka,1883-07-03,1924-06-03,Czech,"Franz Kafka was a German-speaking Bohemian novelist and short-story writer, widely regarded as one of the major figures of 20th-century literature."
27,Daphne,du Maurier,1907-05-13,1989-04-19,British,"Daphne du Maurier was an English novelist, short story writer, and playwright. Many of her works have been adapted into films, including Rebecca."
28,Milan,Kundera,1929-04-01,2023-07-11,Czech,"Milan Kundera was a Czech-born French writer who wrote in Czech and French. He is best known for his novel The Unbearable Lightness of Being."

29,Octavia E.,Butler,1947-06-22,2006-02-24,American,"Octavia E. Butler was an American science fiction writer. A multiple recipient of both the Hugo and Nebula awards, she was the first science fiction writer to receive a MacArthur Fellowship."

30,Philip K.,Dick,1928-12-16,1982-03-02,American,"Philip K. Dick was an American science fiction writer. He wrote 44 novels and about 121 short stories, most of which appeared in science fiction magazines."

31,Ursula K.,Le Guin,1929-10-21,2018-01-22,American,"Ursula K. Le Guin was an American novelist, short story writer, poet, and literary critic. She was best known for her works of fantasy and science fiction."
32,Neil,Gaiman,1960-11-10,null,British,"Neil Gaiman is an English author of short fiction, novels, comic books, graphic novels, nonfiction, audio theatre, and films."
33,Terry,Pratchett,1948-04-28,2015-03-12,British,"Terry Pratchett was an English humorist, satirist, and author of fantasy novels, most notably the Discworld series."

34,George R.R.,Martin,1948-09-20,null,American,"George R.R. Martin is an American novelist and short-story writer in the fantasy, horror, and science fiction genres, and a screenwriter and television producer."
35,Stephenie,Meyer,1973-12-24,null,American,"Stephenie Meyer is an American author. She is best known for her Twilight series of novels, which have sold over 100 million copies worldwide."
36,Suzanne,Collins,1962-08-10,null,American,"Suzanne Collins is an American television writer and novelist, best known as the author of The Hunger Games series."
37,Veronica,Roth,1988-08-19,null,American,"Veronica Roth is an American novelist and short story writer, known for her debut New York Times bestselling Divergent trilogy."
38,John,Green,1977-08-24,null,American,"John Green is an American author and YouTube content creator. He won the 2006 Printz Award for his debut novel, Looking for Alaska."
39,Cassandra,Clare,1973-07-27,null,American,"Cassandra Clare is an American author of young adult fiction, best known for her bestselling series The Mortal Instruments."
40,Rick,Riordan,1964-06-05,null,American,"Rick Riordan is an American author. He is known for writing the Percy Jackson & the Olympians series, about a demigod son of Poseidon."

41,E.B.,White,1899-07-11,1985-10-01,American,"E.B. White was an American writer. He was the author of several highly popular books for children, including Stuart Little, Charlotte's Web, and The Trumpet of the Swan."
42,Roald,Dahl,1916-09-13,1990-11-23,British,"Roald Dahl was a British novelist, short story writer, poet, and screenwriter. His books have sold more than 250 million copies worldwide."
43,Dr.,Seuss,1904-03-02,1991-09-24,American,"Dr. Seuss was an American children's author, political cartoonist, illustrator, poet, animator, and filmmaker. He is known for his more than 60 books."

44,Beatrix,Potter,1866-07-28,1943-12-22,British,"Beatrix Potter was an English writer, illustrator, natural scientist, and conservationist best known for her children's books featuring animals, such as The Tale of Peter Rabbit."
45,A.A.,Milne,1882-01-18,1956-01-31,British,"A.A. Milne was an English author, best known for his books about the teddy bear Winnie-the-Pooh and for various poems."

46,C.S.,Lewis,1898-11-29,1963-11-22,British,"C.S. Lewis was a British writer and lay theologian. He held academic positions in English literature at both Oxford and Cambridge Universities. He is best known for his Chronicles of Narnia."

47,J.R.R.,Tolkien,1892-01-03,1973-09-02,British,"J.R.R. Tolkien was an English writer, poet, philologist, and academic, best known as the author of the high fantasy works The Hobbit and The Lord of the Rings."
48,Frank,Herbert,1920-10-08,1986-02-11,American,"Frank Herbert was an American science fiction author best known for the 1965 novel Dune and its five sequels."

49,Isaac,Asimov,1920-01-02,1992-04-06,American,"Isaac Asimov was an American writer and professor of biochemistry at Boston University. He was known for his works of science fiction and popular science."

50,Arthur C.,Clarke,1917-12-16,2008-03-19,British,"Arthur C. Clarke was a British science fiction writer, science popularizer, futurist, and inventor. He is best known for the novel 2001: A Space Odyssey."
